-- Alcatel-Lucent CEO Is Said to Step Down in May, Le Monde Says
-- B y   K e n n e t h   W o n g
-- 2013-02-06T22:19:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-06/alcatel-lucent-ceo-is-said-to-step-down-in-may-le-monde-says.html
Alcatel-Lucent SA  Chief Executive
Officer  Ben Verwaayen , whose term ends this year, won’t have his
mandate renewed and will step down May 7, Le Monde  reported ,
without citing anyone.  The decision was made at a board meeting today, the
newspaper said. Alcatel-Lucent is scheduled to release fourth-
quarter earnings tomorrow before the market opens in France.  Simon Poulter , a spokesman for the Paris-based company,
said the company wouldn’t comment on speculation.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kenneth Wong in Berlin at 
